{
  "stem": "11744.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I say that this might be one of the reason why we were never-- we were never treated badly, because we were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, I was never called a dirty Jew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I never-- anything like this happen to me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And being French for so many generations, we were profoundly French, and I lived a life of all the French girls.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I went to the scouts for years and years, and I-- I used to do fencing, and I had everything like everybody else-- piano lesson, dancing lesson, and everything else.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was a really normal kind of a life-- not prepared at all for anything drastic happening, having no-- no experience whatsoever until the first refugees came-- started to come from Germany and from Austria, were telling impossible stories to believe.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the only answer we had was, oh, this is OK.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's in Germany and in Austria.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's never going to be in France.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, my God-- when I was married already.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No-- I mean, the first refugees came after 1933, and Hitler started-- I mean in 1933, then '34, '35, '36.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, people who could get out tried to get out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so we heard-- we heard impossible stories that were not easy to believe.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we always had that same reaction-- it can happen to them, it can never happen to us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I was growing up, I had a brother and when I was eight and a half years old I got a sister.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I have a brother and a sister, and that's it-- and my parents.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father worked, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my father was in a shoe business, and he was that all his life.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And involved in a lot of things, in a lot of different-- different organization.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
